dcterms:description: The Multi-Atlas Labelling Challenge (MALC) dataset consists of 30 T1 MRI volumes of the brain, each from a different subject. All scans have an isotropic resolution of 1mm3. It is used for training the model with a 5-fold cross-validation approach.
dcterms:title: MALC Dataset

dcterms:description: The ADNI-29 dataset consists of 29 scans from the ADNI dataset, with a balanced distribution of Alzheimer’s Disease and control subjects, and scans acquired with 1.5T and 3T scanners. The presence of pathology makes the segmentation task challenging.
dcterms:title: ADNI-29 Dataset

dcterms:description: The CANDI dataset consists of 13 brain scans of children (age 5-15) with psychiatric disorders. Some scans have severe motion artifacts.
dcterms:title: CANDI Dataset

dcterms:description: The Visceral dataset consists of 20 annotated contrast-enhanced whole-body CT scans with a voxel resolution of 2mm3. It is used for segmenting 14 organs from the thorax and abdomen.
dcterms:title: Visceral Dataset
